    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows two spheres. Each sphere is positioned at the top of a vertical insulating stand. Sphere X has a charge of positive 2 Q, and Sphere Y has a charge of positive 4 Q.\" src=\"/images/77c4793197f24d65cb2b99d06abeb4c4.svg\"></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Two identical conductive spheres are attached to insulating stands. Sphere <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></math></span></span> initially has a charge of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive 2 Q\"><math alttext=\"positive 2 Q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>Q</mi></math></span></span>, and Sphere <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\"><math alttext=\"Y\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi></math></span></span> initially has a charge of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive 4 Q\"><math alttext=\"positive 4 Q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>Q</mi></math></span></span>, as shown in the figure. The two spheres are brought into contact and are then separated. Which of the following correctly compares the change in charge on Sphere <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></math></span></span> and the change in charge of the two-sphere system?</p><div class=\"table_wrapper\"><table class=\"tgroup align:center cols:3 colsep:0 frame:none rowsep:0\"><colgroup><col class=\"colspec align:center colname:col1 colnum:1 colsep:1 colwidth:35\"><col class=\"colspec align:center colname:col2 colnum:2 colwidth:100\"><col class=\"colspec align:center colname:col3 colnum:3 colwidth:150\"></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\"><tr class=\"row